12 §2864. Duties of pharmacy benefit managers
13 A. A pharmacy benefit manager shall owe owes a fiduciary duty to the
14 beneficiaries of any pharmacy benefit management plan administered by the
15 pharmacy benefit manager and to the entities that have entered into a contract with
16 the pharmacy benefit manager the duties of good faith, honesty, trust, confidence,
17 and candor and shall discharge that duty in accordance with the provisions of state
18 and federal law.
19 B. The standard for the fulfillment of a pharmacy benefit manager's duties
20 shall be to act with a high degree of care, skill, prudence, and diligence required of
21 a reasonable and prudent person with substantial experience and expertise in the
22 management of pharmacy benefit management plans and payment of claims. A
23 pharmacy benefit manager shall perform its fiduciary duty with care, skill, prudence,
24 and diligence, and in accordance with the standards of conduct applicable to a
25 fiduciary in an enterprise of a like character and with like aims.
26 (1) A pharmacy benefit manager shall notify the beneficiaries or contracted
27 entities to which it acts as a fiduciary in writing of any activity, policy, or practice
28 of the pharmacy benefits manager that directly or indirectly presents any conflict of
29 interest with the duties imposed by this Section.
