HB 919 Original 2026 Regular Session Echols
Abstract: Requires pharmacy benefit managers to reimburse under-reimbursed dispensing
fees. Restricts pharmacy benefit mangers from assigning reimbursement costs to
plans or members. Prohibits pharmacy benefit managers from operating a pharmacy
that the pharmacy benefit manager or its subsidiaries is contracted by or owned.
Establishes duties of a pharmacy benefit manager.
Present law provides for pharmacy benefit manager rebate retention restrictions and fee
disclosures.
Proposed law adds that pharmacy benefit managers shall reimburse under-reimbursed
dispensing fees. Provides that proposed law shall have prospective and retroactive
application.
Proposed law restricts pharmacy benefit mangers from assigning reimbursement costs to
plans or members.
Proposed law prohibits pharmacy benefit managers from operating a pharmacy that is owned
or contracted by a pharmacy benefit manager or its subsidiaries.
Proposed law provides guidelines for pharmacy benefit managers dispensing fees.
Proposed law imposes penalties for pharmacy benefit managers violations.
Proposed law establishes duites of pharmacy benefit managers.
